cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically the biases present in word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves developing algorithms to modify the embeddings, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential amplification of biases, which is relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of metrics and evaluation methods falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society), and the development of algorithms to remove biases can also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
